## Performance Optimization

### Concurrent Requests

**Gotenberg handles concurrent requests** efficiently.

**Best practices**:
- Use connection pooling
- Limit concurrent requests (avoid overwhelming server)
- Implement request queuing for high volume
- Monitor response times

**Recommended concurrency**: 10-20 concurrent requests per Gotenberg instance.

### Caching Strategies

**Cache generated PDFs** when possible.

**When to cache**:
- Static reports (don't change frequently)
- Invoices (immutable after generation)
- Documents with consistent content

**When NOT to cache**:
- Personalized content (user-specific data)
- Real-time reports (frequently changing data)
- Documents with timestamps

**Cache key considerations**:
- Include all input parameters
- Version cache when templates change
- Set appropriate TTL (time-to-live)

### Resource Limits

**Gotenberg has resource limits** to prevent abuse.

**Common limits**:
- Request size (typically 50-100 MB)
- Conversion timeout (typically 30-60 seconds)
- Concurrent requests per instance

**Optimization tips**:
- Split large documents into smaller chunks
- Compress images before conversion
- Use appropriate page sizes (A4 vs. custom)
- Minimize HTML complexity

### Async Processing

**For long-running conversions**, use async patterns.

**Pattern**:
1. Submit conversion request
2. Return job ID immediately
3. Poll for completion
4. Retrieve PDF when ready

**Benefits**:
- Non-blocking API calls
- Better user experience
- Handles timeouts gracefully

