## Common Use Cases

### Invoices

**Generate invoices from HTML templates**.

**Requirements**:
- Company logo (inline as base64)
- Line items table
- Total calculations
- Footer with payment terms
- Professional styling

**Template structure**:
```html
<!-- Header with logo and company info -->
<!-- Invoice details (number, date, due date) -->
<!-- Customer details -->
<!-- Line items table -->
<!-- Subtotal, tax, total -->
<!-- Footer with payment terms -->
```

### Reports

**Generate analytical reports**.

**Requirements**:
- Charts and graphs (embed as images or SVG)
- Tables with data
- Page numbers
- Table of contents
- Headers and footers

**Considerations**:
- Use page breaks (`page-break-after: always`)
- Set print-friendly styles
- Test with different page sizes

### Receipts

**Generate customer receipts**.

**Requirements**:
- Transaction details
- Payment method
- Timestamp
- QR code (for mobile receipts)
- Compact layout

**Best practices**:
- Use smaller page size (half-letter or custom)
- Minimal styling for fast generation
- Include transaction ID for reference

### Contracts

**Generate legal contracts from templates**.

**Requirements**:
- Multiple pages
- Signature blocks
- Terms and conditions
- Page numbers
- Legal disclaimers

**Considerations**:
- Use consistent formatting
- Test page breaks
- Include revision history
- Add watermarks for drafts

